{
  "stem": "1033.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 55.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "One day I was walking in the basement of the orphanage-- and I was practically born this way, afraid of my own shadow-- and suddenly I see the director, and I just wanted to disappear.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I am walking along, and I suddenly feel his arm on my shoulder, and he planted a big kiss on my face.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then he kept walking.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "As long as I live, I'll never forget this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You know, I still-- I'm on the verge of crying just to remember it, how-- how wonderful it is to be-- to be courageous enough to show affection.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Because I think that's what everyone needs, really, whether we admit it or not.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So-- and there was the sewing place where our clothes were issued.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "There was a lady called Mrs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Pfeiffer, who was a cripple, but a very feisty person.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And she was always critical.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We were kneeling too much, or we were sliding on our behinds, or we weren't taking care of our clothes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We had two sets of clothes-- one to wear in the building, one in-- uniforms both-- one in which we marched to school.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And you could see, we were in the [NON-ENGLISH] Budapest-- a very elegant area, close to the Liget.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "You could see four, five, six kids marching, all in black uniform with black caps in the morning, going to school, and at noon.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Coming back from school.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It had an ethos all of its own.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And-- and-- it was-- you know, I really learned to love this place.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I became friendly with a boy my age called Steven Proper.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And his father was a-- a scout master, and they were on some sort of outings, and the boat turned over, and the kids fell in, and the father jumped in to save them-- and they all got drowned.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Including the father.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he came in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and six, seven months, we were in the same class.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We became very close friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was a-- if possible, he was even more shy than I was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Quiet man.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's-- unfortunately, I found out some years back that he had a brain tumor, and he committed suicide.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I do have a picture of him in my album.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He left a little girl who I was unable to trace.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Anti-Semitism was always there, like a cloud.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a terrible feeling.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I never, ever felt like a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I still don't feel like a Jew.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I feel like me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I-- I naturally, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] think of myself, and feel that I belong to the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I-- I-- I don't know if it's a fair classification.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And who said that fear has ever been an issue of-- of trying to group people?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I often make the analogy of talking about people with size eight shoes, or with blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's-- it's-- it's been terribly unfair.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I think of what this fear did to my own mother, you know, it's useless for me to speculate how it could have been, had she been well and strong.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she wasn't well, and she wasn't strong.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And really, this is something that had never, ever been-- in my purview, it was out of my own hands.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember my grandfather used to go to a place called [NON-ENGLISH], the place where my mother was eventually hospitalized.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Not too often, maybe five times a year.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he used to come back with little red hats for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was the-- what the young Hungarian soldiers wore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember at school, the-- in fact the sons of the teacher who was teaching me, kept shouting at me, shouting, Jewish [HUNGARIAN]-- which means, look, what a joke, a Jewish soldier.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- I just-- I just ran.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It seems to me so much of my life-- and I find that most regrettable-- had been lived in flight.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I do notice various kinds of flight patterns right now, right here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You don't have to be Jewish to know what I'm talking about.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And anti-Semitism, of course, was more than registered for me as-- as my life unfolded, albeit that it is a happy kind of finish, for which I am profoundly grateful.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in the orphanage, we heard stories.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We heard people running away from Czechoslovakia, from Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had some kids in the orphanage-- smf we were so cruel, because these kids didn't speak Hungarian, they spoke Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they used to say [YIDDISH]-- and-- which means where are you from?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we used to call them 'Finns' among ourselves-- which is an awful thing to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
